title: Public invited to consultation sessions on future health care service delivery model
content_text:
p>Members of the public are invited to attend consultation sessions on August 17 
and 18 to express their views on the future service delivery model for Hong 
Kong's health care system.  The Health and Medical Development Advisory Committee (HMDAC) had issued a 
discussion paper entitled "Building a Healthy Tomorrow". The paper seeks to set 
out the views of the committee on the future service delivery model for Hong 
Kong�� s health care system with a view to building a sustainable system that is

Kong�� s health care system with a view to building a sustainable system that is 
accessible and affordable by every member of the community.  The Secretary for Health, Welfare and Food, Dr York Chow and members of the 
HMDAC will attend the two public consultation sessions to collect public views 
and answer public enquiries.  The first session will be held at 10.30am on August 17 (Wednesday) at Wei Hing 
Theatre, 6/F, Amenities Building, City University of Hong Kong, Tat Chee Avenue,

Kowloon Tong.  The second session will be held at 2.30pm on August 18 (Thursday) at Leighton 
Hill Community, 133 Wong Nai Chung Road, Hong Kong.  The discussion paper is obtainable from District Offices, public hospitals and 
clinics, Maternal and Child Health Centres, Elderly Health Centres and Woman 
Health Centres. It can also be downloaded from

Health Centres. It can also be downloaded from http://www.hwfb.gov.hk/hmdac/. Seats will be arranged on a first come, first served basis. For enquiry, please call telephone no. 2871 8787 during office hours.
